David wrote:
> >         We are working on the implementation of DHCP Client(linux) for
> > a TCP/IP stack which has multiple interfaces.
> >
> > According to the RFC 2131, Page 21, Section 3.6
> >    "A client with multiple network interfaces must use DHCP through each
> >    interface independently to obtain configuration information parameters for
> > those separate interfaces."
I believe that the ISC dhcp client does this plus much more.   I use:
dhcp-client-3.0-alpha-19990423  Have a look at
ftp://ftp.isc.org/isc/dhcp/dhcp-3.0-alpha-19990423.tar.gz
  or
ftp://ftp.isc.org/isc/dhcp/dhcp-2.0b1pl26.tar.gz
 .
> Can someone fill me/us in on this?
Try the dhcp-client mailing list.
